<div id="container">

<div id="left-col">
  <h2>Welcome!</h2>

  <div id="video-intro">
   video coming soon
  </div>

  <p>
    This Warper lets you plot scanned maps and images in the geographic space of a digital map. 
    Some people call this process ‘warping’ and some call it ‘geo-rectifying’. 
    Confused? don’t worry! Just watch the video or go to <a href="#">(link)</a> for 
    tutorials and examples.  You can also <a href="#">post your questions</a> to the 
    global MapStory community.
  </p>

  <p>
    The Warper makes it easy to incorporate historical maps and 
    imagery - like aerial photos - into your 
    MapStory projects. Its free to use...so enjoy! 
  </p>

  <div id="tag-cloud">
    <h4 class="smaller">Tags</h4>
    <% tag_cloud @tags, %w(css1 css2 css3 css4) do |tag, css_class| %>
      <%= link_to tag.name, { :controller=>:maps, :action => :tag, :id => tag.name }, :class => css_class %>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="right-col">
  <div id="search-form">
    <%= render :partial => 'shared/search' -%>
</div>

<div id="map_list">
  <h2><%= link_to 'Browse All Maps', maps_path %>
  </h2>

  <% if @my_maps -%>
    <h3>My Maps</h3>
    <table id="map_table" cellpadding="3">
    <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Map</th>
          <th>Title</th>
          <th>Last modified</th>
          <th>Status</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
        <%= render :partial => 'maps/map', :collection => @my_maps  unless @my_maps.nil? %>
    </table>
    <%= link_to "See all of My Maps", my_maps_path(:user_id => current_user) -%>
  <%end -%>

  <br/>

  <h3>Last Rectified Maps</h3>

  <table id="map_table" cellpadding="3">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Map</th>
          <th>Title</th>
          <th>Last modified</th>
          <th>Status</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
    <%= render :partial => 'maps/map', :collection => @maps unless @maps.nil? %>
  </table>

  <%= link_to 'See all Maps', maps_path %>

</div>

<div id="layer_list">

  <h3>Recent Layers</h3>
  <table id="layer_table" cellpadding="3">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Layer</th>
        <th>Title</th>
        <th>Year</th>
        <th>Number of Maps</th>
        <th>Percentage Complete</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <%= render :partial => 'layers/layer', :collection => @layers unless @layers.nil? %>
  </table>
<%= link_to "View all Layers", layers_path %><br />
<%= link_to "Create a new layer", new_layer_path %>
</div>

</div>
<div class="clear"></div>
</div>
